<TITLE> CA returns home after hajj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 24 (bdnews24.com)Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed returned to Dhaka Monday after performing hajj in Saudi Arabia, airport security officials said. The CA landed at Zia International Airport in the morning with wife Neena Ahmed, who had accompanied her husband to Saudi Arabia, ZIA security chief Nurul Islam told bdnews24.com. Fakhruddin left Dhaka on Dec 16 and performed the holy rites at Makkah and Medina as the Saudi King's royal guests, and offered prayers for the welfare, peace and prosperity of Bangladesh. On Dec 20, the chief adviser, accompanied by army chief General Moeen U Ahmed and the Bangladesh envoy to Saudi Arabia, paid a courtesy call on King Abdullah bin Abdul Aziz Al Saud. The same day, they attended the royal reception given by the king in honour of the heads of government and other VIPs performing hajj. Fakhruddin left Makkah Sunday after addressing a gathering of Bangladeshis in Jeddah the same day. Law adviser Mainul Hosein and foreign affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury received the chief adviser. bdnews24.com/e
